# Negative fixture: an exception covers a real gap (the result is not justified
# by a configuration baseline). The exception is complete and independently
# reviewed, but EXPIRED — so once the gate runs with an as-of date past its
# expiry it cannot apply and the gap stays open. Run with --as-of before the
# expiry and the same exception legitimately applies (VALID WITH EXCEPTIONS),
# which is how the advisory workflow proves expiry is actually enforced.
